{
  "texts": [
    "It can be challenging to fully capture the complexities of strategic management settings given the constraints imposed by the fixed structures (Arend, 2022), as exemplified by the stylized NK models (Davis et al., 2007; Levinthal, 1997).",
    "The naive automaton agents in ABMs need to be exogenously pre-determined by the researcher, which means they do not default to approximating human behavior (Ganco, 2017).",
    "Most importantly, these agents cannot verbalize the \"thinking\" behind their decision-making, which limits the researcher's ability to engage in abductive reasoning (Makadok et al., 2018).",
    "None of these challenges apply to in silico experiments using LLMs.",
    "In summary, LLMs have the potential to be used in management research."
  ]
}